update an email law from the past century
steven warshak , a cincinnati businessman who build an empire sell male sexual enhancement drug , be convict of wire fraud several year ago , based in large part on his email correspondence , which authority have extract via a subpoena under a 1986 law govern electronic privacy .
a federal appeal court in ohio later found , however , that the government have violate warshak’s constitutional right to privacy .
the court say investigator should have convince a judge that there be probable cause and obtain a search warrant , as though his message have be stash in a desk drawer .
although the court let the conviction stand , the case highlight the conflict legal rule that govern electronic privacy .
congress be now set to clarify those rule , bring that quarter @-@ century @-@ old law , the electronic communication privacy act , or ecpa , in line with the internet age .
on thursday , the senate judiciary committee will start deliberate a measure that would require the government to get a search warrant , issue by a judge , to gain access to personal emails and all other electronic content held by a third @-@ party service provider .
the current statute require a warrant for emails that be less than 6 month old , but it let the authority gain access to older communication – or bizarrely , emails that have already be open – with just a subpoena and no judicial review .
the law govern the privacy of practically everything entrust to the internet – family photo store with a web service , journal entry keep online , company document uploaded to the cloud , and the flurry of emails exchange every day .
the problem be that it be write when the cloud be just a cumulus in the sky .
silicon valley company as well as advocacy group from the political left and right have be lobby for change for many year , and reform legislation seem to be gain broad political support .
even the justice department appear to have approve one major change : require law enforcement to get a search warrant for all kind of electronic content , no matter how long it have be in electronic storage or what exactly electronic storage mean .
“ change the law have become more of an imperative because of the growth of cloud compute , because everyone include member of congress be store sensitive info with third @-@ party provider and they want it to be protect , ” say greg nojeim , senior counsel at the washington @-@ based center for democracy and technology , which be finance partly by silicon valley company and which be part of a coalition push for reform .
“ the technology be advance and people realize the law have to keep pace.”
update the bill could have a broader impact on civil case as well , clarify who can gain access to emails , photo and facebook post in corporate litigation and divorce court .
it could also lie out clearer rule for government agency like the internal revenue service to follow to gain access to private citizens’ emails .
the agency tell congress recently that it seek search warrant before read taxpayer emails , though its write policy say otherwise , accord to an information request file by the american civil liberty union .
court across the country , apparently baffle by how to apply the exist law , which apply to content hold in “ electronic storage , ” have rule in sometimes contradictory way over the privacy of electronic material in both civil and criminal case .
in one prominent case , lee jennings sue a relative of his wife who broke into his yahoo account and ferret out emails describe an extramarital affair that be later use as incriminate evidence in divorce proceeding .
jennings claim a violation of his privacy under the electronic privacy act , but the highest court in his home state of south carolina hold that his emails , which sat on yahoo’s server , be not hold in “ electronic storage ” and therefore be not cover by the statute .
a federal court in california year earlier have rule differently in another case , interpret “ electronic storage ” far more broadly .
jennings’ lawyer , neal k . katyal , a former act solicitor general in the obama administration , ask the supreme court to reconcile the dueling interpretation .
the court decline to hear the case this month , effectively leave it to congress to clarify the law .
although the appeal court rule in the warshak criminal case be bind only in the 6 th circuit , it have since become the default legal threshold for many web company .
facebook say it turn over content create by user – picture , post , message – only after it be serve with a search warrant , though a subpoena suffice for basic subscriber information , include a user’s name and email address .
twitter , too , say “ request for content of communication require a u.s. search warrant , ” and it inform user when it receive a request for information from a government agency .
microsoft , which operate email and cloud storage service , follow a similar practice , insist on a search warrant for “ content , ” include document , photo , email and instant message .
with a subpoena , the company can divulge a user’s internet protocol record , though , which can be use to establish a person’s location .
“ the law be so old it doesn’t account for how we have turn into a digital society , ” say bryan schilling , a lawyer at microsoft .
he offer an offline analogy : “ if somebody have a storage unit , law enforcement would be require to get a search warrant , ” he say .
“ it’s the same thing now , as we store more and more of our content in the cloud , consumer or enterprise.”
the original sponsor of the 1986 law , sen. patrick leahy , d @-@ vt . , have call its overhaul his top priority for the year .
he and sen. mike lee , r @-@ utah , have introduce a measure require law enforcement to obtain a warrant for all electronic content , include emails , regardless of how old they be .
that overhaul be back by an unlikely coalition .
amazon and google , which offer cloud @-@ based service to consumer and business , be lobby for the change , along with startups like evernote and tumblr , which operate modern @-@ day private diary .
they have join with advocacy group as diverse as the american civil liberty union and americans for tax reform .
the issue of email privacy receive the greatest attention last year , when gen. david h . petraeus , the former director of the central intelligence agency , resign after an inquiry into his email correspondence turn up evidence of an extramarital affair .
he and his biographer , paula broadwell , have exchange amorous correspondence in a “ draft ” folder of a share gmail account , apparently to elude detection .
those draft message , because they have not be transmit across the internet , could have be view by federal authority with nothing more than a subpoena , accord to current law .
george jones in real life and real time
early in 1977 , a couple of year after he and tammy wynette have divorce , the country music star george jones play a show at the stardust inn in waldorf , md . , his first in the washington area in several year .
i be then a young pop music critic at the washington post , so it fall to me to write a profile of the notoriously hard @-@ drink singer .
what follow be an experience so intense , so remarkable for its raw emotional force , that i could not help but think of it friday , when it be announce that jones have die in a nashville , tenn . , hospital at the age of 81 .
that weekend i learn two important thing about jones : that there be very little distance between him and his song , and that the same quality that make him a great artist also make his life a torment .
in those day he be still unashamedly carry a torch for wynette , who have leave him because , as she put it in legal paper she file , he “ drink to such an extent that he become completely and absolutely unmanageable.”
on stage that weekend , he reworked song like “ she think i still care ” and “ picture me without you ” so that they include reference to her , make them almost embarrassingly personal , as if she be in the audience and he be sing only to her .
but it be on his tour bus between set that i see george jones more achingly and nakedly vulnerable than any performer i have ever encounter , before or since that night .
he be dress in a flashy leisure suit and wear a pair of glitter diamond ring on his left hand , include one with his initial , but as he talk about wynette and how much he still love her , he begin to weep .
i don’t think he be drunk .
he talk about how he be try to stay dry for tammy , who by that time have already re @-@ marry and divorce again .
within a year or two , he would develop a cocaine habit that would send his career off the rail , but there be no sign of that either .
this be just george jones in real life and real time .
it be hard today , in a time when irony have become a dominant cultural mode and artist be screen from reporter by phalanx of handler , to imagine so public a breakdown happen or a celebrity let his pain be so visible .
but jones wasn’t ashamed or embarrass by that display , and when he go back to the stage for a second set of what he describe to me as “ sad , sloppy tear @-@ jerkers , ” his sing be even more passionate and inspire , with his twangy , somewhat nasal voice crack in all the right place with what have to be genuine feel , not artifice .
over a career that last nearly 60 year , jones record more than 100 album , and over and over again , he didn’t just sing the song that be give to him .
in the best of his recording , as on that night , he also inhabit them , so that anyone listen to him could be sure : he really mean it , he have really live this song about heartbreak or hangover and know what it mean , poor soul .
as someone who grow up in chicago listen mostly to the blue , i have no special fondness for country music , whose only local outlet in those day be the radio station wjjd .
but see george jones live for the first time that cold night in southern maryland be a revelation , because in his own highly idiosyncratic way he show himself to be no less soulful a singer than howlin’ wolf on something like “ how many more year ” or otis redding on “ i’ve been love you too long.”
despite all the drink and drug binge that would dog his career , jones never lose that gift .
in 2009 , assign to write a profile of the canadian singer @-@ songwriter leonard cohen for this newspaper , i walk into cohen’s new york hotel suite to find him play one of jones’ late @-@ career gem , “ choice , ” on his ipod .
cohen express great admiration for jones and then recite one of the song’s most powerful verse :
i be tempt
by an early age i find
i like drinkin’
oh , and i never turn it down
there be love one
but i turn them all away
now i’m live and die
with the choice i make
@in part because of his consistent “ nip , ” as he call it , jones never enjoy the crossover success of his contemporary johnny cash and merle haggard , and so his pass will probably not have the broad cultural resonance that cash’s do .
but he be , hand down , a superior singer , a fact obvious to everyone in the country music field : as waylon jennings once sang , “ if we all could sound like we want to , we’d all sound like george jones.”
but even within the confine of “ pure country , ” whatever that term might mean today , jones do not stand still .
he begin his career very much in the mold of his idol hank williams , sing tune about honky @-@ tonks and carouse .
he never lose his affection for that genre , but over the year he also evolve into a master of ballad sing , especially on his duet with melba montgomery and wynette , both before and after they be marry .
and though a brief late ‘50 s flirtation with rockabilly didn’t pan out , jones also know how to rock .
it’s almost forget now , but he and elvis presley once be co @-@ headliners on a louisiana hayride tour , and generation of rock ' n’ roll band , include one i play in , have cover song like “ why baby why , ” “ white lightning ” and “ the race is on ” and find them to be guarantee crowd @-@ pleasers .
begin in the 1980 s , jones , with the help of his fourth wife , nancy sepulvedo , pull himself out of his tailspin .
but by then the country music mainstream have begin to move on to more polished style , and jones’ visceral approach fall out of fashion .
in recent year , jones have think of himself as a relic , and express bitterness at what he see as the disregard for what he represent .
all that may be true , but it can’t – and doesn’t – dim the magnificence of his achievement , any more than his personal weakness and demon do .
death row inmate ’ s request for dna test is reject
the state of mississippi reject on monday a request to submit physical evidence for dna test make by a prisoner schedule to be put to death tuesday even .
willie j . man , convict in 1994 of murder two college student , have be repeatedly rebuff in the court as he seek to have dna test perform on certain crime scene evidence .
but the most recent request come about because of two letter send by the justice department in recent day to the prosecutor who handle manning’s trial .
the letter concern the trial testimony of an fbi expert ask to examine “ hair fragment ” find at the scene of the murder .
the expert testify that in this case he could determine only that the hair come from an african @-@ american but that hair comparison analysis be capable , give better sample , of matching a hair to a particular individual .
man be black ; the murder victim be white .
the prosecutor cite this testimony several time in his closing argument .
in a letter date may 2 , the justice department say the expert’s testimony about the general capability of hair analysis – that it could match a hair to a specific individual – be erroneous and “ exceed the limit of the science.”
then , in a letter date may 4 , the department further say that such analysis could not “ determine ” that a hair come from a person of a certain race , as the expert testify at one point , only that the hair “ possess certain trait that be associate with a particular racial group.”
the fbi offer in both letter to perform dna test on the hair fragment .
manning’s lawyer argue that these letter constitute new evidence and thus that the hair , as well as other evidence collect at the scene include a rape kit and fingernail scrapings , should be submit for dna test before man be put to death .
in the response deny the request , the state attorney general , jim hood , call the new request a “ red herring , ” say that the letter do not “ represent new evidence , ” nor do they repudiate the testimony give by the fbi expert in 1994 .
manning’s lawyer be still lobby the governor for a stay of execution .
on friday , manning’s brother and the mississippi innocence project file suit to preserve all the physical evidence for dna test even if the execution be carry out .
