the cause be complication of metastatic liver cancer , mario gallucci , mastromarino’s lawyer , say .
the technology that allow the transplantation of critical organ also enable the far more common transplantation of tissue : bone can be use to repair fracture , vein for heart bypass surgery , and tendon and ligament can restore mobility .
harvest organ be allow in new york state , provide the donor do not carry a potentially communicable disease , the survivor approve and the person be not too old .
but there be nowhere near enough willing donor to meet the demand for tissue , so the profit from one body can reach six figure .
mastromarino become license by new york state to supply tissue bank and manufacturer of biological surgical instrument after his dental license be suspend in 2002 because of a drug addiction .
he establish a network of undertaker , whom he pay up to $ 1,000 per corpse , and soon take on assistant and form a business based in new jersey , biomedical tissue service .
he reportedly make $ 10,000 to $ 15,000 per body .
but mastromarino harvest organ and tissue from body without consent from the survivor , the authority say , and remove material from people with cancer , hiv and other disease .
he then forge paperwork , include consent form and death certificate , to make the cause of death and age acceptable .
the police begin investigate irregularity at the daniel george & son funeral home in bensonhurst , brooklyn , in 2005 .
