no special session , but protester leave capitol
time @/@ herald tallahassee bureau
tallahassee — they weren’t able to persuade gov . rick scott to call a special session on the controversial ''stand your ground’' law .
but the student activist know as the dream defender draw national attention to their cause by hold the longest sit @-@ in demonstration at the florida capitol in recent memory .
on thursday , the miami @-@ based group announce that their record @-@ set protest be over — for now , at least .
''after 31 day and 30 night , we be leave the capitol for our next phase , '' dream defender executive director phillip agnew say .
agnew say the group would register thousand of new voter in the come month and return to the capitol for legislative committee hearing in the fall .
the dream defenders’ occupation of the capitol begin july 16 , three day after george zimmerman be acquit in the shoot death of trayvon martin , an unarm teenager from miami @-@ dade .
they promise to stay until scott convene a special session on ''stand your ground’' and several other criminal justice issue .
''we say if ( scott ) would not give us a seat at the table , we would sleep on the floor until ( he ) give us what we deserve , '' agnew say .
scott meet with the protester july 18 but refuse their demand .
the dream defender try to persuade state lawmakers to call the session themselves , but they couldn’t muster the 96 vote need .
as of thursday , 42 lawmakers have vote in favor of hold the session , 90 vote against , and 28 have yet to vote .
this week , house speaker will weatherford call for the group’s departure .
the dream defender claim several victory , include a promise from weatherford to hold a hear on the ''stand your ground’' law this fall .
the group also secure meeting with the florida department of law enforcement to discuss racial profile , agnew say , and begin a dialogue with the state department of juvenile justice on the disproportionate number of young african @-@ american men in prison .
agnew say the dream defender have not be pressure to wrap up their protest by the governor’s office or state law enforcement official .
the capitol police who have watch over the group , agnew add , ''deserved a raise.''
the state spent a total of $ 153,630 on police overtime throughout the protest , accord to fdle .
the dream defender didn’t anticipate their stay would last a month or that singer harry belafonte , rapper talib kweli or civil right leader jesse jackson and julian bond would join them in the capitol .
''gov . scott , through his inaction , create a new group of leader who will have a lasting effect on florida , '' say state rep . alan williams , a tallahassee democrat who mentored the group .
when they pack up their belongings and leave the capitol thursday even , the young activist wonder aloud if there have be some level of divine intervention along the way .
on wednesday , the state department of management service announce plan to test the fire alarm system in the capitol .
the test would last from 8 p.m . until midnight , and involve an ''incredibly loud , high @-@ pitch noise , '' accord to a press release .
but before the test begin , the build adjacent to the capitol be struck by lightning .
the department of management service decide to perform maintenance on that building’s fire alarm system instead .
''i don’t know how to explain it , '' dream defender steven pargett say .
''some thing be just meant to happen.''
