a pink @-@ slip thank for a major decision
on baseball ) ;
when john gaherin , the chief labor negotiator for major league baseball , arrive for a meet with the chief of the player union and baseball’s arbitrator , he carry an envelope in the pocket of his suit jacket .
it be two day before christmas 1975 , not a time to be conduct serious business , but gaherin and marvin miller , the executive director of the union , know why peter seitz , the arbitrator , have summon them .
they know that the subject of the meet would be as serious a bit of business as baseball have ever experience , and gaherin go to the meet prepare .
seitz have informally telegraph his decision in a grievance case , and now he would formally hand his write opinion to the two men .
as soon as he do , gaherin hand seitz the envelope .
“ you’re fire , ” it say in effect .
such be the perilous life of impartial arbitrator in baseball and other professional sport .
either side - the league or the union - have the right to fire them .
like manager , they be hire to be fire .
“ he tell me he have expect as much , ” michael seitz , peter’s son , say in a recent telephone interview .
“ his feel be there be no other way to decide the case , because the baseball owner have be stupid in assume that when they didn’t have a player under contract , they still have a contractual hold on him.”
fredric r . horowitz , a 64 @-@ year @-@ old lawyer from santa monica , calif . , be the latest to take a turn .
he will arbitrate alex rodriguez’s appeal of his 211 @-@ game suspension .
while arbitrator pay for their decision , which anger either the owner or the player , they don’t always receive credit for the significance of their decision .
seitz , for example , be responsible for create free agency in baseball with his decision in the 1975 andy messersmith @-@ dave mcnally grievance , but i believe , as marvin miller use to complain , that some report in the news media , include in the new york time , mistakenly credit other case : curt flood’s 1970 lawsuit against baseball and catfish hunter’s 1974 grievance against charlie finley .
flood’s suit challenge the game’s reserve clause , the rule that bound a player to his team until he be trade , sell or release .
hunter’s grievance contend that finley , the oakland athletics’ owner , have breach his contract .
the hunter case be exactly what the union argue , a breach @-@ of @-@ contract case .
finley have not pay the premium on hunter’s annuity , as stipulate in his contract , richard moss , the union lawyer , say , and the pitcher should be a free agent as a result .
seitz , in his first year as baseball’s arbitrator , agree with moss’ argument and declare hunter a free agent .
a year later , when seitz rule in the messersmith @-@ mcnally grievance , he do not cite the hunter decision as a basis for this decision .
as a breach @-@ of @-@ contract case , it affect no player but hunter .
no other player could gain free agency based on seitz’s decision on hunter .
“ it didn’t change the mind of a single owner , ” miller say of the hunter decision in one of the many conversation we have on the subject .
" the owners’ position on free agency be the same after the hunter case as it be before.''
nor , miller add , do the flood case affect the owners’ think on the reserve clause and free agency .
the reserve clause have forever be the tie that bound player to their team , whether they like it or not .
flood do not like it , and when the st . louis cardinal trade him to philadelphia , he opted to sue the commissioner rather than go to the phillies , contend that he should have the right to play where he want .
the suit go all the way to the u.s. supreme court , where flood lose .
the owner always argue that elimination of the reserve clause would ruin baseball , miller say , and flood’s loss in the lawsuit embolden them to maintain their position .
as heroic as flood be in pursue his lawsuit , it fall well short of have an effect .
its failure be one of the reason the owner be so confident of winning the messersmith @-@ mcnally grievance in court when they appeal seitz’s decision , which say player could be free agent if they play the renewal year in their contract without sign a new contract .
what the owner fail to understand , in their inexperience in labor matter , be that judge rarely overrule an arbitrator’s decision , do so only if an arbitrator’s authority have be exceed .
the club and the commissioner have not do particularly well before arbitrator in instance where player have be suspend for conduct off the field .
that history continue last year when shyam das overturn ryan braun’s 50 @-@ game suspension .
das be fire after his braun rule .
baseball would have prefer settle all of the dope case stem from the investigation into biogenesis , an anti @-@ aging clinic that be believe to have distribute ban substance to baseball player .
the union also seem eager to settle .
but rodriguez have appeal his 211 @-@ game suspension .
given the volatility of the rodriguez case , it would not be surprising if horowitz’s first major case be his last .
