protest as city college close a student center
julie turkewitz contribute report .
new york - it be just a small room , one of hundred in city college’s north academic center , but over the year the guillermo morales @/@ assata shakur student and community center have take on a significance beyond its square footage .
to student organizer who use it as their meet space , it be a place for lesbian and gay activist , women’s right group , community organization and others to make common cause .
to outside critic it be a symbol of campus politics gone berserk , its unofficial name a glorification of city college alumni who have join revolutionary organization and gone on the lam .
but official at city college , part of the city university of new york , insist that charge history be not a factor when they decide that the room would be better use as an annex for the school’s career service office , two floor below .
without notice , security officer enter the room this past weekend , box up and remove its content - and just to be on the safe side , lock down the entire build , include the library .
with just a day to go before midterm exam , the library be reopen after a few hour .
but room 3 @/@ 201 be not , result at least for a brief while in the incongruous sight of close door emblazon with a bold , black fist , below a crisp white sign that read career and professional development .
( the door have be repaint , without the fist , as of monday afternoon.)
given the center’s history , it could not have come entirely as a surprise when its former occupant let their dissatisfaction be know .
they organize protest rally , distribute flier , post video and demand that city college be shut down .
a protester be arrest .
and just in time for an outdoor demonstration on monday , someone set off a fire alarm , send hundred of people out onto the plaza .
“ i think that the cuny administration be really scare of a lot of the organize and community @-@ build come out of the build , ” say alyssia osorio , director of the morales @/@ shakur center .
“ we provide so many service for the community - know @-@ your @-@ right train , a farm share that provide healthy food , we’ve run a soup kitchen , we have provide baby @-@ sit service for people in the community.”
deidra hill , vice president of communication at city college , call the administration’s takeover of the room a matter of space .
she say the career service office need a quiet area where student can “ meet with outside employer , with alumni , to seek advice on careers.”
city college say the unusually swift action be necessary .
“ we be concern that we might have to move people , and that would not have be safe , ” hill say .
as for the protest , “ student be exercise their free speech right , which the college support , ” she say .
the city college student whom the center’s name honors have never visit .
guillermo morales , a leader of the faln , a puerto rican independence group that claim responsibility for a deadly bomb in new york , flee to cuba .
so do shakur , who as a member of the black liberation army be convict in the 1973 kill of a new jersey state trooper .
in 2006 , a student object to the name of the center .
in the ensue controversy , cuny’s chancellor order that it be change .
but it stick .
taf sourov , 19 , a member of the revolutionary student coordinating committee , a group that regularly meet there , say he believe the closing be retaliation for student protest against david h . petraeus , the former cia director and military commander , who be teach a course at the macaulay honors college .
“ i practically live out of the room , ” sourov say .
“ i would do my homework in there .
i do my political work in there .
i would socialize in there .
i feel like part of me be rip out.”
