similarly , state official have also complain that state prison be hold thousand of undocumented immigrant who be convict of state crime .
at one point last year , well over 12,000 state convict have deportation detainers on them -- mean that as soon as they complete their sentence or be parole they be subject to be deport , official say .
most be mexican citizen , prison official say .
proposal to deport convict serve time for nonviolent crime before they be parole have fail to gain support from legislative leader , who fear if they be parole and return home they would simply slip back across the border into texas .
the savings from that plan be estimate to be at least $ 15 million , official say at the time .
