scott’s list of rejection include :
* benjamin crump of tallahassee , a criminal defense lawyer honored by the naacp for his legal advocacy and who be best know for his firm’s representation of the family of trayvon martin .
* lynn drysdale , a consumer protection lawyer with jacksonville area legal aid who have testify before congress in opposition to state law that allow payday lender to target military personnel .
* w.c . gentry , a high @-@ profile trial lawyer in jacksonville who be a member of the legal ''dream team’' that successfully sue the tobacco industry in the 1990 s .
a former county school board member , he have generously contribute to democratic candidate and have give money to republican , too .
* tiffany faddis , a trial lawyer , board member of the trial bar’s statewide lobby arm , the florida justice association , incoming president of the hispanic bar association of central florida and a register republican .
antonacci say lawyer with such background be more likely to have a ''living constitution’' view of the law as evolve and ever @-@ change , which he say be at odds with scott’s view .
he say he do not know what the florida bar’s agenda be in choose which lawyer to send to scott , and defend the practice of reject bar name .
''the florida bar be not an accountable organization in any electoral way , '' antonacci say .
''the accountability in the process be with the governor.''
a spokeswoman for the bar , francine walker , say : ''the florida bar respect that the governor can reject nominee it submits.''
deirdre macnab , president of the league of women voter of florida , criticize scott’s frequent pattern of reject bar @-@ support lawyer .
''i believe it’s unprecedented , '' macnab say .
''this be a pretty blatant example of politicize the court , and citizen should be concern .
… it’s disheartening.''
macnab serve on a statewide judicial nominate panel for federal judge and be appoint by u.s. sens . bill nelson , a democrat , and marco rubio , a republican .
former republican state sen. alex villalobos of miami , president of democracy at stake , a bipartisan group that advocate an independent judiciary , say he regret vote more than a decade ago to weaken the bar’s role in judicial selection .
prior to that , the bar have three automatic slot on every jnc .
''that be a mistake , '' he say .
''we’re reap what we sowed.''
antonacci say the pace of rejection be likely to quicken , because term of 78 jnc member be schedule to expire by june .
all 78 be appoint by scott’s predecessor and likely 2014 opponent , crist .
since become governor in 2011 , scott have appoint more than 100 judge statewide .
