advisory for tuesday , sept. 24 th @ 10 am
mine worker and supporter to encircle peabody hq in downtown st . louis
union say retirees and dependents must receive health care benefit earn during decade of labor in company mine
st . louis – thousand of mine worker and supporter plan to march around the headquarters of peabody energy in st . louis this come tuesday , sept. 24 th .
the event be the latest in a series of protest direct at the world’s largest private @-@ sector coal company , which report $ 90 million in net income in the second quarter of 2013 .
peabody executive , however , be so far refuse to honor the company’s obligation to provide critically need health care benefit for retire miner .
who : mine worker and supporter , include :
· cecil roberts , international president , umwa
· hugh mcvey , president , missouri afl @-@ cio
· terrence melvin , president , coalition of black trade unionist
· claude cummings , vice president , cwa district 6
· rev . jonathan stratton , episcopal diocese of missouri
what : march encircle peabody headquarters , call for the company to honor its obligation to retire miner and their dependents .
when : tuesday , september 24 th , 10 am ( central time )
where : march to begin at crowne plaza hotel , 200 n . fourth street .
marcher will proceed on pine st . to broadway , to market .
then on market street to circle around peabody headquarters along market , eighth , chestnut and seventh street .
marcher will then proceed to kiener plaza for a rally .
“ the patriot coal chapter of this fight be behind us , now it’s time for peabody energy and arch coal to meet their responsibility , ” say umwa president roberts .
last month , uwma member approve a settlement with patriot coal , a company create by peabody in 2007 , which among other provision establish a mechanism for payment of health care benefit for retire miner .
however , long @-@ term fund for those benefit have not be secure .
the union also win a court rule in august establish peabody’s continue obligation to 3,100 miner and dependents , whose benefit remain with peabody at the time of the patriot spinoff .
arch coal , another profitable company , dump its retiree obligation into a company call magnum coal in 2005 .
magnum be subsequently acquire by patriot , which enter bankruptcy reorganization last year .
“ this fight be anything but over , ” say roberts .
“ executive of these company have to understand that miner and their family know the real story of what happen here – and because of our effort , so do million of work people across the country .
men and women work underground for decade to earn these benefit .
these company be profitable , and they must step up to meet their obligation to these retirees.”
the union’s ongoing effort to win full benefit for all affect retire miner include a lawsuit against peabody and arch , file in west virginia ; legislation in congress to aid retire miner and their dependents , sponsor by both republican and democrat ; and an ongoing public education , advertise and community action campaign .
additional information be available at fairnessatpatriot.org .
