afghan may face death for alleged conversion
a man in afghanistan be be prosecute in a kabul court and could be sentence to death after be charge with convert from islam to christianity , a crime under the country 's islamic sharia law , a judge say sunday .
the trial highlight a struggle between religious conservative and reformists over what shape islam will take here four year after the ouster of the islamic fundamentalist taliban regime .
the defendant , abdul rahman , 41 , be arrest last month after his family accuse him of become a christian , accord to judge ansarullah mawlavezada .
