vancouver pot activist marc emery to plead guilty to u.s. drug charge
no hope of avoid extradition , plea deal make
marc emery be face extradition on three drug charge for sell marijuana seed by mail order to customer in the u.s. ( cbc )
marijuana activist marc emery say he plan to drop his fight against extradition to the u.s. and plead guilty to one charge of drug distribution in a seattle courtroom next month .
emery 's extradition hear in vancouver be adjourn on wednesday so his lawyer could negotiate a deal with the u.s. district attorney in which emery could spend up to eight year in jail for one charge , while two other more serious charge be drop , he say .
" i will be make a guilty plea to one count of marijuana distribution this summer , and then when i 'm sentence the u.s. district attorney be go to be ask for five to eight year in a federal u.s. penitentiary , " he tell cbc news on wednesday .
after the guilty plea , emery expect he will be sentence in august or september and be hope he will eventually be transfer to a canadian jail .
joint u.s. @-@ canada bust
this be not the first time the marijuana activist have say his lawyer be cut a deal with u.s. prosecutor .
in july 2008 , emery say he have make a deal in which he would serve a minimum of five year in jail , but he later blame canadian authority when the deal fall through .
the marijuana activist be face drug charge for sell pot seed to u.s. customer , after his vancouver @-@ based mail order business be bust in a joint operation involve both u.s. and canadian law enforcement agency in 2005 .
he 's be fight extradition ever since , but on wednesday he say he now realize it 's a fight he 's not go to win .
" ultimately my lawyer be convince that the canadian government have never refuse an extradition request from the unite state and it 's not go to start now , " he say .
" sometimes you have to face up to the reality of what 's go to happen , and under this scenario i may be free out of prison in two or three or four year , " he say .
without the deal , emery say , he would be face much more time in jail .
" this be a preferential arrangement to the not @-@ so @-@ good @-@ arrangement that would see me spend 10 , 20 , 30 year in a u.s. federal penitentiary , foreseeably the rest of my life , and that do n't give a person a lot of hope , " he say .
prepare to do time
" the da want to paint me as a large player provide a lot of marijuana to people , and we 'll bring up that it be only seed and it be totally transparent .
it be do in canada out in the open for 10 or 12 year , " he tell cbc news during an interview at the busy downtown vancouver hemp store he still operate .
" i do n't keep any of the money — $ 4 million .
i give it all away to activist group around the world , so my motive be unusual , so that do mitigate in sentence , " say emery , who frequently run in provincial and federal election as the leader of the marijuana party .
but the man who once spend more than two month in a canadian prison for pass a joint to an undercover officer be now prepare for a much long stay in a u.s. prison .
" you 've get to keep busy in jail .
you 've get to be read , in my case write .
i 'll be learn spanish , french .
you 've get to have project , " he say .
